The article discusses President Biden's congratulatory message to the Libyan people on the establishment of a Government of National Unity. The government will lead Libya to national elections on December 24, 2021. The article emphasizes the importance of democratic processes and the opportunity for Libyans to choose their leaders. It also mentions the need to regain sovereignty, free from foreign interference and violence, after years of civil conflict and political upheaval. The United States expresses support for the electoral roadmap and vows to hold accountable any parties that undermine it. The article calls for the withdrawal of foreign mercenaries and weapons, urging a peaceful political transition. It encourages Libyans to resolve their differences peacefully, establish law and order, and create a stable and prosperous future for themselves.